title: Accelerator pedal position 2
description: Accelerator Pedal position 2 sensor short circuit to battery
action:
- The accelerator pedal position circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage in the accelerator pedal position 2 circuit, valid range is between 575 - 2075 mV
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 5V
- Measure the grounding of the accelerator pedal position 2 circuit, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace accelerator pedal
cause: The controller measures a voltage above 2425mV for at least 100ms on pin 55 of connector A
effect:
- When only accelerator pedal position 2 is faulty, the machine will go into limp home mode (reduced functionality to go to the workshop)
- When both accelerator pedal positions are faulty, the engine will only run at low idle speed
- The accelerator pedal position 2 is a safety critical input, therefor the fault will only be reset after a key cycle

title: Park brake pressure sensor
description: Park brake pressure sensor short circuit to ground
action:
- The park brake pressure sensor circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the current of the park brake pressure sensor, valid range is between 4 and 20 mA
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be equal to KL15 voltage
- Replace park brake pressure sensor
cause: The controller measures a current below 1000 µA for at least 100ms on pin 66 of connector A
effect:
- The park brake telltale will blink at 2 Hz in the dashboard view
- The park brake status will be broadcasted as "Error" on the CAN bus, therefor 3rd party systems (Engine, Transmission, etc) may report faultcodes as well
search_terms: Park brake pressure sensor short circuit to ground

title: OI Time out error
description: OI Message TimeOut error
action:
- When the OI Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the OI Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the OI CAN message for 50s from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine the water in fuel status, since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the water in fuel telltale and pop-up won't be activated.

title: EFLP1 Time out error
description: EFLP1 Message Timeout error
action:
- When the EFLP1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the EFLP1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the EFLP1 CAN message for 1500ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine the engine oil  pressure status, since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the engine oil pressure too high and too low won't be activated.

title: TRF1 Time out error
description: TRF1 Message TimeOut error
action:
- When the TRF1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the transmission configuration

- When the TRF1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Transmission Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the transmission controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the TRF1 CAN message for 5000 ms from the transmission on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine the transmission oil sump sump temperature, since  the data is not received from the transmission. Therefor the transmission sump oil temperature too high won't be activated.

title: EEC1 Message TimeOut error
description: EEC1 Message TimeOut error
action:
- When the EEC1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the EEC1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the EEC1 CAN message for 250ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine the engine speed, engine torque and engine start mode, since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the faults in relation to these signals won't be activated.

title: ETC1 time out error
description: ETC1 Message TimeOut error
action:
- When the ETC1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the transmission configuration

- When the ETC1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Transmission Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the transmission controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the ETC1 CAN message for 500 ms from the transmission on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine the transmission driveline engaged and input shaftspeed, since  the data is not received from the transmission. Therefor the faults in relation to these signals won't be activated. Note: in most configurations is the controller unable to calculate vehicle speed

title: Differential lock state - central rear
description: Differential lock state - central rear short circuit to battery
action:
'- The diff lock engaged circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V
- Measure the grounding of the diff lock proximity sensor or switch, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace diff lock proximity sensor or switch
cause: The controller measures a voltage above 965mV for at least 100ms on pin 46 of connector B. Note: faultcode is only applicable for a diff. lock proximity sensor configuration and not for a diff. lock switch
effect: When the differential lock state can't be determined by the controller, the system won't be able to display the current state.
search_terms: Differential lock state - central rear short circuit to battery

- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V
- Measure the grounding of the diff lock proximity sensor or switch, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace diff lock proximity sensor or switch
cause: The controller measures a voltage below 50mV for at least 100ms on pin 46 of connector B. Note: faultcode is only applicable for a diff. lock proximity sensor configuration and not for a diff. lock switch
effect: When the differential lock state can't be determined by the controller, the system won't be able to display the current state.

- Measure the current of the service brake pressure sensor, valid range is between 4 - 20mA
- Measure the grounding of the service brake pressure circuit, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace service brake pressure sensor

effect: The controller is not able to determine the service brake pressure, therefor the controller can't determine if the brake pedal is pressed. Functions depending on the service brake might work

title: KL50 relay
description: KL50 high side output short circuit to battery
action:
- The engine start circuit is partly described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2 and partly described in the Electic Diagram of the engine
- Measure the voltages in engine start circuit to find the short circuit to battery
- Measure the voltages in the engine start circuit to find the open load
- Check the fuses in the engine start circuit
- Replace KL50 engine start relay
cause: The controller measures a current below 500mA for at least 100ms on pin 18 of connector A
effect:
The engine may not stop cranking, when the ignition if on.  Or the engine doesn't crank.
Note: the Volvo engine start via CAN
search_terms: KL50 high side output short circuit to battery

title: KL50 relay
description: KL50 high side output short circuit to ground
action:
- The engine start circuit is partly described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2 and partly described in the Electic Diagram of the engine
- Measure the voltages / resistance in engine start circuit to find the short circuit to ground
- Replace KL50 engine start relay
cause: The controller measures a current above 1000mA for at least 100ms on pin 18 of connector A
effect:
The engine doesn't crank.
Note: the Volvo engine start via CAN
search_terms: KL50 high side output short circuit to ground

title: SHUTDN Time out error
description: SHUTDN Message TimeOut error
action:
- When the SHUTDN Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the SHUTDN Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the SHUTDN CAN message for 5000 ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine wait to start lamp status since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the wait to start telltale won't be shown on the display

title: Parking trailer brake air pressure sensor
description: Parking Trailer Brake Air Pressure sensor current below normal or open circuit
action:
- The air pressure circuit 3 is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the current of the air presssure circuit 3  sensor, valid range is between 4 - 20mA
- Measure the grounding of the air pressure circuit 3 , make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace air pressure circuit 3
cause: The controller measures a voltage below 1mA for at least 100ms on pin 8 of connector B
effect: The controller is not able to determine the pressure of air circuit 3, therefor the controller can't broadcast the pressure to other systems. Functions depending on the air pressure of circuit 3 may function incorrect
search_terms: Parking Trailer Brake Air Pressure sensor current below normal or open circuit

description: Air Pressure Circuit 1 short circuit to battery
action:
- The air pressure circuit 1 is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage in the air pressure circuit 1, valid range is between 1000 - 4000 mV
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V
- Measure the grounding of the air pressure circuit 1, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace air pressure circuit 1 sensor

effect: The controller is not able to determine the pressure of air circuit 1, therefor the controller can't broadcast the pressure to other systems and determine the brake pressure for the front axle. Functions depending on the air pressure of circuit 1 may function incorrect.

title: AT1T1I1 Time out error
description: AT1T1I1 Message TimeOut error
action:
- When the AT1T1I1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration
- When the AT1T1I1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the AT1T1I1 CAN message for 5000ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine the DEF level and DEF level low indicator, since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the display is not able to show information in relation to the diesel exhaust fluid

title: Work light front cabin
description: Work Light Cabin Front output short circuit to battery
action:
- The work light front circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltages in work light front circuit to find the short circuit to battery
- Measure the voltages in the work light front circuit to find the open load
- Check the fuses in the work light front circuit
- Replace work light front
cause: The controller measures a current below 20mA for at least 100ms on pin 81 of connector A
effect: The controller is not able to control the work light front, therefor the work light front may or may not illuminate. A short to circuit to battery may result in a group switch 2 error and may deactivate outputs 73 - 81 of connector A.
search_terms: Work Light Cabin Front output short circuit to battery

title: 5th wheel joystick sensor 1
description: 5th Wheel Lift Lower Joystick 1 sensor short circuit to battery
action:
- The 5th th wheel joystick circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage in the 5th wheel joystick signal 1 circuit, valid range is between 4500 - 500 mV
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 5V
- Measure the grounding of the 5th wheel joystick signal 1 circuit, make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace 5th wheel joytstick
cause: The controller measures a voltage above 4750mV for at least 100ms on pin 67 of connector A
effect:
- When only one of the two joystick signals is faulty, the 5th wheel can still be operated 
- When both joystick signals are faulty, the 5th wheel can't be operated anymore
- The 5th wheel joystick is a safety critical input, therefor the fault will only be reset after a key cycle
search_terms: 5th Wheel Lift Lower Joystick 1 sensor short circuit to battery

1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)

cause: The controller determines an issue on pin 28 or 41 of connector A. Specific root cause can't be determined. Potential hardware, software, firmware or configuration issue
effect: 5th wheel lock control will be blocked by a safety function.

title: Sensor supply 5 volt
description: Sensor Supply 5 Volt short circuit to battery
action:
- The 5V supply circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltage valid range is between 4900 mV - 5100mV
- Check fuses that supply 24V of the controller
cause: The controller measures a voltage above 5100mV for at least 100ms on pin 31 of connector A
effect: The controller can't supply the sensors with 5V supply, therefor sensors and switches may report errors

title: Brake light
description: Brake Light output short circuit to battery
action:
- The brake light circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltages in brake light circuit to find the short circuit to battery
- Measure the voltages in the brake light circuit to find the open load
- Check the fuses in the brake light circuit
- Replace brake light
cause: The controller measures a current below 20mA for at least 100ms on pin 78 of connector A
effect: The controller is not able to control the brake light, therefor the brake light may or may not illuminate. A short to circuit to battery may result in a group switch 2 error and may deactivate outputs 73 - 81 of connector A.
search_terms: Brake Light output short circuit to battery

title: Brake light
description: Brake Light output short circuit to ground
action:
- The brake light circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the voltages / resistance in brake light circuit to find the short circuit to ground
- Replace brake light
cause: The controller measures a current above 250mA for at least 100ms on pin 78 of connector A
effect: The controller is not able to control the brake light, therefor the brake light may not illuminate.
search_terms: Brake Light output short circuit to ground

title: Emergency stop failure
description: 1 of the 2 emergency inputs is incorrect
action:
The emergency shutdown circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the suppply voltage, this must be 24V
- Measure the voltage on 42B and 43B, these must be equal to the supply voltage, when the buttons are released and 0V, when closed
- Both inputs must have the same outcome (open or closed)
- Replace emergency button
cause: The controller measures voltage between 200mV and 500mv for at least 100ms on PIN 42B or 43B.
effect: When the emergency button input state can't be determined by the controller, the emergency button may won't be able to stop the vehicle operation in emergency cases
search_terms: 1 of the 2 emergency inputs is incorrect

title: DPFC1 Time out error
description: DPFC1 Message Time out error
action:
- When the DPFC1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the DPFC1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the DPFC1 CAN message for 5000 ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine aftertreatment regeneration status since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the aftertreatment regeneration statusb  won't be shown on the display

title: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor
description: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor short circuit to battery
action:
- The transmission converter out temperature circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the resistance in the transmission converter out temperature circuit, valid range is between 20 Ohm - 40000 Ohm
- Measure the grounding  make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace sensor
cause: The controller measures a resistance below 20 Ohm for at least 100ms on pin 47 of connector A
effect: The controller can't determine the temperature of the transmission converter out temperature. Therefore the actual temperature and the temperature warnings will not be shown
search_terms: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor short circuit to battery

title: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor
description: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor short circuit to ground
action:
- The transmission converter out temperature circuit is described in Electric Diagram of the YTCC2
- Measure the resistance in the transmission converter out temperature circuit, valid range is between 20 Ohm - 40000 Ohm
- Measure the grounding  make sure the ignition is inactive
- Replace sensor
cause: The controller measures a voltage above 40000 Ohm for at least 100ms on pin 47 of connector A
effect: The controller can't determine the temperature of the transmission converter out temperature. Therefore the actual temperature and the temperature warnings will not be shown
search_terms: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor short circuit to ground

title: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor
description: Transmission torque converter temperature sensor root cause not known
action:
- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.
cause: The controller determines an issue on pin 47 of connector A. Specific root cause can't be determined. Potential hardware, software, firmware or configuration issue
effect: The controller can't determine the temperature of the transmission converter out temperature. Therefore the actual temperature and the temperature warnings will not be shown

title: DLCC1 Time out error
description: DLCC1 Message TimeOut error
action:
- When the DLCC1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the engine configuration

- When the DLCC1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Engine Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)
2) Check power supply, fusing and grounding of the engine controller and/or engine related subsystems
cause: The controller has not received the DLCC1 CAN message for 5000 ms from the engine on the J1939 CAN bus
effect: The controller can't determine engine lamp status since  the data is not received from the engine. Therefor the engine malfunction lamps  won't be shown on the display

action:

- When the ETC7 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Transmission Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)

cause: The controller has not received the ETC7 CAN message for 1000 ms from the transmission on the J1939 CAN bus

title: Reference engine torque
description: Signal error
action:
- When the EC1 Time out faultcode is the only time-out faultcode, Check the transmission configuration

- When the EC1 Time out faultcode is accompanied by Transmission Node Time out faultcode:
1) Check J1939 CAN bus wiring e.g. short circuit between CAN high and CAN low, CAN bus termination not correct (60O when ignition off)

cause: The controller has not received the engine reference torque correctly from the engine
effect: The transmission can't determine the shiftings point correctly

title: Hella intelligent battery sensor (IBS) CAN node
description: The YTCC detected that the status message from the Hella IBS is not available on the TB1CAN bus indicating that the Hella IBS CAN node is not available
action: Open the CAN Network check menu and check if the IBS is available on the CAN Network. If the IBS is not available, not active or error check the CANbus, LINbus and power supply of the IBS. Also check if the LIN to CAN converter is operational. If it is available check if any message from source address 0x1E is present on the TB1CAN bus. If there is a message on the TB1CAN bus from the source address mentioned before check if the YTCC is operational. When the YTCC is operational try flashing the vehicle with the latest software set available for the vehicle. Try replacing the LIN to CAN converter, try replacing the IBS
cause: The YTCC did not receive any CAN messages from the Hella IBS CAN node within a certain timeframe
effect: The YTCC is unable to determine the status of the 24V BMS. Without this information, optimalisation of the charging strategy for the 24V battery is not possible
search_terms: Hella intelligent battery sensor (IBS) CAN node

title: Steering control error
description: Unintended steering
action: Re-calibrate the DBW steering control. When something is wrong with the steering angle sensors, this will be noticed during calibration as well.
cause: In DBW mode, the requested steering angle is not reached or the steering angle did not move fast enough towards the requested steering angle. Perhaps something is wrong with the steering angle sensors or the steering calibration is off.
effect: Protective stop will be triggered, automatic steering will be blocked

title: Steering control error
description: PVED-CLS operating state invalid
action:
Please check if the PVED is powered on and check if it is still properly connected to the TB2 CAN bus. This can be checked via the CAN network check menu on the display. In case the PVED is on and connected to the TB2 CAN, please contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.
cause: The steering controller is not in autonomous mode, while the vehicle is in DBW mode. This is most likely caused by a safe state triggered in the steering controller. It might be, but is less likely erratic CAN requests transmitted to the steering controller.
effect: Protective stop will be triggered in DBW mode

title: Steering control error
description: Condition Exists
action: Please check if the PVED is powered on and check if it is still properly connected to the TB2 CAN bus. This can be checked via the CAN network check menu on the display. If this all looks ok, swapping the PVED might be needed.
cause: Something is wrong with the steering controller (PVED). It might be powered off, or not correctly communicating on the TB2 CAN bus. It is also possible the PVED is defect.
effect: Speed limit of 5 km/h is activated in manual mode. Protective stop is activated in DBW mode.

title: Park brake release - pressure too low
description: Pressure is smaller than 540 kpa while park brake is released
action: Check for air leaking from the pneumatic system. You should be able to hear air leaking. Otherwise swap the park brake pressure sensor
cause: Perhaps the park brake pressure sensor is faulty, or there might be a leak in the pneumatic system.
effect: Speed limit of 5 km/h is activated in manual mode. Protective stop is activated in DBW mode.
search_terms: Park brake release - pressure too low
Pressure is smaller than 540 kpa while park brake is released

title: Park brake pressure released too fast
description: The park brake pressure has been released too fast
action: Please check if the throttle valve has been installed in the electronic park brake system. Check for air leaking from the pneumatic system. You should be able to hear air leaking. Otherwise swap the park brake pressure sensor
cause:
The throttle valve might be missing in the park brake pneumatic system. The park brake pressure sensor might be faulty  or there might be a leak in the pneumatic system.

Note: please prevent cycling the park brake request any faster than 3 seconds as this will not give the pneumatic system enough time to reach some pressure points and will likely trigger a pressure monitoring safety function.
effect: Speed limit of 5 km/h is activated in manual mode. Protective stop is activated in DBW mode.
search_terms: Park brake pressure released too fast
The park brake pressure has been released too fast

title: Steering power monitoring
description: No power due to engine off
action:
This is fueltype specific:
Diesel: Please start the engine. 

EV: Please check if the hydraulic pump is running (EAMS message on J1939)

If the steering power monitor function keeps failing, please check the hydraulic piping
cause:
This cause is fueltype specific:
Diesel: The engine is not running, therefore there is no hydraulic pressure.

EV: The hydraulic pump is not running
effect: Power steering is disabled which in turn causes automatic steering to be in error
search_terms: No power due to engine off

title: Unintended 5th wheel unlock detected
description: Condition Exists

Please check the locked status sensor (pin 28 or / and 41 of the A connector)

If those are ok, please check if the trailer  / the connecting system is mechanically sound
cause:
An untended unlock (= trailer state from coupled to not coupled without an unlock request) has been detected.

cause: CAN bus load exceeded 80%

title: J1939 CAN-bus
description: Bus off
action: Please check the wiring of this CAN bus. of the ATCC2 Pin 48 is CAN low, and pin 49 is CAN high. You can also measure the resistance of the CAN bus when the vehicle is turned off. The resistance should be 60 Ohm. When this is 120 Ohm, a terminal resistor can be missing. If the wiring and resistance is all ok, you could disconnect components from the CAN bus one by one, and check when the error gets resolved. If it gets resolved after disconnecting a component, probably the baud rate of this component is wrong.
cause: Possibly a wire break, missing terminal resistor or a component added to the CAN bus which is transmitting on a different Baud rate than 250k
effect: No communication is possible on this CAN bus. The vehicle cannot be operated properly.

description: Bus load warning
action:
'- Contact the aftersales department for support via the portal

In order to facilitate adequate support please supply the following information:
1) Detailed description of failure e.g. specific reproducable trigger conditions or behavior (reoccurs every key cycle or from a certain speed etc)
2) Log file from DIM, of the faulty scenario
3) Photo or movie of the behavior or of the DIM e.g. Dashboard view, Faultcodes view, IO Check view, CAN network check view, About menu view
4) Updated software or parameter set recently, from Terberg or 3rd party systems e.g. Engine, Transmission? If so, please supply us with details.
cause: CAN bus load exceeded 80%
effect: Communication reliability on the CAN becomes critical. Data transmitted on the CAN bus can get lost.

title: AT1 CAN-bus
description: Bus off
action: Please check the wiring of this CAN bus. of the ATCC2 Pin 53 is CAN low, and pin 54 is CAN high. You can also measure the resistance of the CAN bus when the vehicle is turned off. The resistance should be 60 Ohm. When this is 120 Ohm, a terminal resistor can be missing. If the wiring and resistance is all ok, you could disconnect components from the CAN bus one by one, and check when the error gets resolved. If it gets resolved after disconnecting a component, probably the baud rate of this component is wrong.
cause: Possibly a wire break, missing terminal resistor or a component added to the CAN bus which is transmitting on a different Baud rate than 500k
effect: No communication is possible on this CAN bus. The vehicle cannot be operated properly.
